Reasoning: 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely category as the paper deals with dynamic networks and their properties, which are often studied in the context of social and information networks. 
- cs.SD (Software Engineering) is also a possible category as the paper discusses the impact of the chosen time scale on the obtained graph series, which is relevant to software engineering practices. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is another possible category as the paper deals with the propagation of link streams, which can be seen as a system that evolves over time. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a possible category as the paper presents an automatic method to determine the saturation scale of any link stream, which involves designing algorithms and data structures. 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is also a possible category as the paper deals with networks and their properties, which are often studied in the context of networking and internet architecture.
